iter90: add MII_CTRL1000 master/prefer-master/manual/1000FD

Per Codex deep research from openwrt-devel mail-archive msg67875:
the vendor SDK init sequence post-cal includes a MII_CTRL1000 write
that the cjdelisle bundle is missing. Without it the user-port PHY
auto-negotiates as slave or skips 1000FD which leaves the MAC RX
in a state where it physically cannot decode frames from the cable.

0x1E00 = ENABLE_MASTER(0x1000) | AS_MASTER(0x0800)
       | PREFER_MASTER(0x0400) | ADVERTISE_1000FULL(0x0200)

--- a/gsw/mt7530.c
+++ b/gsw/mt7530.c
@@ -1259,5 +1259,9 @@ en751221_setup_port(struct dsa_switch *ds, int port)
 
 	en751221_pgsel_mmd_write(phy, MDIO_MMD_VEND1, 0x00a6, 0x0350);
 
+	/* iter90: MII_CTRL1000 master/prefer-master/manual/1000FD - missing in
+	 * cjdelisle bundle; per Codex from mail-archive msg67875 */
+	phy_write(phy, MII_CTRL1000, 0x1E00);
+	dev_warn(ds->dev, "ITER90: setup_port port=%d MII_CTRL1000=0x1E00\n", port);
 	phy_write(phy, MII_BMCR, BMCR_ANENABLE | BMCR_ANRESTART);
 }
